### Hadith 3:211

*Narrated Abu 'Ubaid:*

(the slave of Ibn Azhar) I witnessed the 'Id with 'Umar bin Al-Kattab
who said, Allah's Apostle has forbidden people to fast on the day on
which you break fasting (the fasts of Ramadan) and the day on which you
eat the meat of your sacrifices (the first day of 'Id ul Fitr and 'Id
ul-Adha).

